 Tim Burton on AI recreations of his style: “It's like a robot taking your humanity” https://www.nme.com/news/film/tim-burton-on-ai-recreations-of-his-style-like-robot-taking-your-humanity-3496163?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=tim-burton-on-ai-recreations-of-his-style-like-robot-taking-your-humanityAdam Starkey Mon, 11 Sep 2023 15:45:04 +0000 Film NewsNews https://www.nme.com/?p=3496163 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="蒂姆·波顿" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> The director described AI imitations of his work as “disturbing”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/tim-burton-on-ai-recreations-of-his-style-like-robot-taking-your-humanity-3496163">Tim Burton on AI recreations of his style: “It&#39;s like a robot taking your humanity”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="蒂姆·波顿" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/Tim-Burton-main-new-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/tim-burton">Tim Burton</a> has described recreations of his work by artificial intelligence as “disturbing”.</p><p> The director, who is known for his macabre visual style across films like <em>Edward Scissorhands</em> and <em>The Nightmare Before Christmas</em> , recalled how he felt when seeing this style replicated by AI.</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE:<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/christina-ricci-joins-tim-burton-addams-family-series-3187596">The best (and worst) Tim Burton films</a></strong></li></ul><p> “They had AI do my versions of Disney characters!” Burton said in mock horror to the <a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/art/features/tim-burton-beetlejuice-2-johnny-depp-disney-b2406538.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Independent</em></a> , in reference to a <a href="https://www.buzzfeed.com/laurengarafano/disney-movies-reimagined-to-be-tim-burton-directed" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Buzzfeed</em></a> article from July this year. “I can&#39;t describe the feeling it gives you. It reminded me of when other cultures say, &#39;Don&#39;t take my picture because it is taking away your soul.&#39;”</p><p> While Burton acknowledged that some of the recreations were “very good”, which included a gothic-looking <em>Frozen</em> , the director largely found looking at imitated art to be a soul-sucking experience. </p><figure id="attachment_3334177" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3334177" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3334177" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Tim-Burton-on-Disney.jpg" alt="蒂姆·波顿" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Tim-Burton-on-Disney.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Tim-Burton-on-Disney-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Tim-Burton-on-Disney-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Tim-Burton-on-Disney-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Tim-Burton-on-Disney-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Tim-Burton-on-Disney-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3334177" class="wp-caption-text"> Tim Burton – CREDIT: Getty</figcaption></figure><p> “What it does is it sucks something from you,” Burton added. “It takes something from your soul or psyche; that is very disturbing, especially if it has to do with you. It&#39;s like a robot taking your humanity, your soul.”</p><p> Earlier this year,<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/wes-anderson-is-not-a-fan-of-his-viral-tiktok-trend-3454631">Wes Anderson expressed how he rejects AI recreations of his work</a> following a viral <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/tiktok">TikTok</a> trend.</p><p> “I&#39;m very good at protecting myself from seeing all that stuff,” Anderson told <a href="https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/wes-anderson-please-do-not-send-me-memes-of-people-doing-me-rzcxbdx0t" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Times</em></a> . “If somebody sends me something like that I&#39;ll immediately erase it and say, &#39;Please, sorry, do not send me things of people doing me.&#39;</p><p> “Because I do not want to look at it, thinking, &#39;Is that what I do? Is that what I mean?&#39; I don&#39;t want to see too much of someone else thinking about what I try to be because, God knows, I could then start doing it.”</p><p> Burton <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/tim-burton-takes-aim-at-disney-calling-it-a-horrible-big-circus-3334174">previously said his “days with Disney are done”</a> following his experience on 2019&#39;s <em>Dumbo</em> , describing working for the company as a “horrible big circus”.</p><p> The director&#39;s next project is <em>Beetlejuice 2</em> , a sequel to his original 1988 film with Michael Keaton back in the lead role. Filming on the project was <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/film-features/strike-actors-writers-hollywood-when-will-it-end-3477098">halted due to the Hollywood actors&#39; strike</a> , two days before it was scheduled to wrap.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/tim-burton-on-ai-recreations-of-his-style-like-robot-taking-your-humanity-3496163">Tim Burton on AI recreations of his style: “It&#39;s like a robot taking your humanity”</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
